  "texts": [
    "Despite significant advancements in DL, applying it to fossil image analysis presents notable challenges.",
    "A primary concern is the reliance on extensive, accurately labeled datasets for model training and testing.",
    "Compiling and annotating these datasets demands considerable time and expert knowledge, which can be a limiting factor in developing robust DL models.",
    "The quality and volume of these training data are crucial, as they directly impact the model's performance and susceptibility to overfitting -a scenario where the model performs well on training data but fails to generalize on unseen data.",
    "Another critical hurdle in deploying DL models lies in their interpretability."
  ],
